# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Project .gitignore — for projects under 02 - Projects/Personal/<Project>
#
# Defaults below treat _meta/ as Obsidian-managed working notes:
#   - AI session logs and meeting notes are NOT committed by default
#     (they often contain sensitive context). Remove the lines below
#     to commit them.
#   - Asset binaries are excluded; markdown attachments still tracked.
#   - Common dev cruft (node_modules, .env, dist, __pycache__, etc.)
#     is excluded so this gitignore works whether the repo root is
#     code, notes, or a mix.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Obsidian / project notes ---
# Private working notes — AI session transcripts may contain secrets,
# meeting notes may contain stakeholder-confidential material.
_meta/AI-Sessions/
_meta/Meetings/

# Project helper / builder skills — imported per-developer, not shared.
# These are workflow helpers (kickoff, wrap-up, etc.), NOT project deliverables.
# If a project's deliverable IS a skill, remove or comment out these lines.
.claude/skills/
.agents/skills/

# Asset binaries (uncomment git-lfs config instead if you prefer LFS)
_meta/Assets/*.png
_meta/Assets/*.jpg
_meta/Assets/*.jpeg
_meta/Assets/*.gif
_meta/Assets/*.pdf
_meta/Assets/*.mp4
_meta/Assets/*.mov
_meta/Assets/*.zip

# Obsidian local state (vault-level — usually not present in project folders,
# but ignore defensively in case of nested vaults or copied state)
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/cache

# --- Secrets ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
secrets.json
credentials.json

# --- Node ---
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
.npm/
.pnp.*

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.venv/
venv/
env/
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# --- Build artifacts ---
dist/
build/
out/
target/
*.log
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# --- IDE / editor ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# --- OS ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/
